comments: From 19 to 168 inclusive, these are the numbers that 'fool' the strong pseudoprimality test described in Wilf (1986) in regards to determining whether 169 is composite or not. - Alonso del Arte, Feb 05 2012
references: Herbert S. Wilf, Algorithms and Complexity. Englewood Cliffs, New Jersey: Prentice-Hall (1986): 158 - 160
